TO: MELVIN J. LASKY

CC, 1 p.





Montreux, April 4, 1966

Palace Hotel

Dear Mr. Lasky,

Legate, I come to you in tears:

My cohorts ordered home!

I've lived in England forty years

What shall I do in Rome?





This Kipling bit that I loved in my boyhood is to introduce the account of a rather silly situation I 